    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "type": "ContextOfUse",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "CPB operating envelope: flow 1–7 L/min, speed 1500–3500 RPM",
      "description": "Bounded operating envelope for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump in CPB service. Volumetric flow rate: 1.0–7.0 L/min (five nominal test points: 1, 2, 3.5, 5, 7 L/min). Rotational speed: 1500–3500 RPM (three nominal speeds: 1500, 2500, 3500 RPM). Inlet pressure: 5–15 mmHg. Outlet pressure: 60–120 mmHg. Blood temperature: 20–37 °C. Haematocrit: 30–45%. Impeller tip clearance: 0.10–0.30 mm (nominal 0.20 mm ± 0.05 mm manufacturing tolerance). All CFD simulations and experimental validation runs fall within these bounds; boundary-point cases at 1 L/min / 3500 RPM and 7 L/min / 1500 RPM are explicitly included in the validation dataset."
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Applicability constraint: Class II CPB centrifugal pumps, adult patients",
      "description": "The credibility assessment applies exclusively to Class II centrifugal blood pumps used for adult cardiopulmonary bypass (patient weight ≥ 40 kg, BSA ≥ 1.5 m²). The FDA generic pump geometry (impeller diameter 50 mm, volute angle 15°) is the reference design; pumps deviating more than ±10% in any principal dimension are outside scope. Paediatric CPB, ventricular assist device (VAD) use, and extracorporeal membrane oxygenation (ECMO) circuits are explicitly excluded. The hemolysis model (power-law Giersiepen–Wurzinger formulation) is valid only for shear-exposure times between 1 ms and 700 ms; operating conditions producing exposures outside this range are out of scope."
    }
  },
